dStorageContainment.AssemblyIsolationByRoamingUser> and <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageContainment.DomainIsolationByRoamingUser> specify a permission to use isolated storage for a roaming user."},{"pos":[5860,5873],"content":"Secure Access","linkify":"Secure Access","nodes":[{"content":"Secure Access","pos":[0,13]}]},{"content":"Using isolated storage enables partially trusted applications to store data in a manner that is controlled by the computer's security policy.","pos":[5875,6016]},{"content":"This is especially useful for downloaded components that a user might want to run cautiously.","pos":[6017,6110]},{"content":"Security policy rarely grants this kind of code permission when you access the file system by using standard I/O mechanisms.","pos":[6111,6235]},{"content":"However, by default, code running from the local computer, a local network, or the Internet is granted the right to use isolated storage.","pos":[6236,6373]},{"content":"Administrators can limit how much isolated storage an application or a user has available, based on an appropriate trust level.","pos":[6375,6502]},{"content":"In addition, administrators can remove a user's persisted data completely.","pos":[6503,6577]},{"content":"To create or access isolated storage, code must be granted the appropriate <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph> permission.","pos":[6578,6729],"source":" To create or access isolated storage, code must be granted the appropriate <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission> permission."},{"content":"To access isolated storage, code must have all necessary native platform operating system rights.","pos":[6731,6828]},{"content":"The access control lists (ACLs) that control which users have the rights to use the file system must be satisfied.","pos":[6829,6943]},{"content":".NET Framework applications already have operating system rights to access isolated storage unless they perform (platform-specific) impersonation.","pos":[6944,7090]},{"content":"In this case, the application is responsible for ensuring that the impersonated user identity has the proper operating system rights to access isolated storage.","pos":[7091,7251]},{"content":"This access provides a convenient way for code that is run or downloaded from the web to read and write to a storage area related to a particular user.","pos":[7252,7403]},{"content":"To control access to isolated storage, the common language runtime uses <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph> objects.","pos":[7405,7550],"source":"To control access to isolated storage, the common language runtime uses <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission> objects."},{"content":"Each object has properties that specify the following values:","pos":[7551,7612]},{"content":"Allowed usage, which indicates the type of access that is allowed.","pos":[7616,7682]},{"content":"The values are members of the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageContainment&gt;</ph> enumeration.","pos":[7683,7787],"source":" The values are members of the <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageContainment> enumeration."},{"content":"For more information about these values, see the table in the next section.","pos":[7788,7863]},{"content":"Storage quota, as discussed in the preceding section.","pos":[7867,7920]},{"content":"The runtime demands <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph> permission when code first attempts to open a store.","pos":[7922,8059],"source":"The runtime demands <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission> permission when code first attempts to open a store."},{"content":"It decides whether to grant this permission, based on how much the code is trusted.","pos":[8060,8143]},{"content":"If the permission is granted, the allowed usage and storage quota values are determined by security policy and by the code's request for <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph>.","pos":[8144,8346],"source":" If the permission is granted, the allowed usage and storage quota values are determined by security policy and by the code's request for <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission>."},{"content":"Security policy is set by using the .NET Framework Configuration Tool (Mscorcfg.msc).","pos":[8347,8432]},{"content":"All callers in the call stack are checked to ensure that each caller has at least the appropriate allowed usage.","pos":[8433,8545]},{"content":"The runtime also checks the quota imposed on the code that opened or created the store in which the file is to be saved.","pos":[8546,8666]},{"content":"If these conditions are satisfied, permission is granted.","pos":[8667,8724]},{"content":"The quota is checked again every time a file is written to the store.","pos":[8725,8794]},{"content":"Application code is not required to request permission because the common language runtime will grant whatever <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph> is appropriate based on security policy.","pos":[8796,9012],"source":"Application code is not required to request permission because the common language runtime will grant whatever <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission> is appropriate based on security policy."},{"content":"However, there are good reasons to request specific permissions that your application needs, including <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph>.","pos":[9013,9181],"source":" However, there are good reasons to request specific permissions that your application needs, including <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission>."},{"pos":[9216,9248],"content":"Allowed Usage and Security Risks","linkify":"Allowed Usage and Security Risks","nodes":[{"content":"Allowed Usage and Security Risks","pos":[0,32]}]},{"content":"The allowed usage specified by <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph> determines the degree to which code will be allowed to create and use isolated storage.","pos":[9250,9433],"source":"The allowed usage specified by <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission> determines the degree to which code will be allowed to create and use isolated storage."},{"content":"The following table shows how the allowed usage specified in the permission corresponds to types of isolation and summarizes the security risks associated with each allowed usage.","pos":[9434,9613]},{"content":"Allowed usage","pos":[9616,9629]},{"content":"Isolation types","pos":[9630,9645]},{"content":"Security impact","pos":[9646,9661]},{"content":"No isolated storage use is allowed.","pos":[9797,9832]},{"content":"There is no security impact.","pos":[9833,9861]},{"content":"Isolation by user, domain, and assembly.","pos":[9948,9988]},{"content":"Each assembly has a separate substore within the domain.","pos":[9989,10045]},{"content":"Stores that use this permission are also implicitly isolated by computer.","pos":[10046,10119]},{"content":"This permission level leaves resources open to unauthorized overuse, although enforced quotas make it more difficult.","pos":[10120,10237]},{"content":"This is called a denial of service attack.","pos":[10238,10280]},{"pos":[10374,10520],"content":"Same as <ph id=\"ph1\">`DomainIsolationByUser`</ph>, but store is saved to a location that will roam if roaming user profiles are enabled and quotas are not enforced.","source":"Same as `DomainIsolationByUser`, but store is saved to a location that will roam if roaming user profiles are enabled and quotas are not enforced."},{"content":"Because quotas must be disabled, storage resources are more vulnerable to a denial of service attack.","pos