f:System.IO.IsolatedStorage.IsolatedStorageScope&gt;</ph> is an enumeration that enables you to create and select a store with the appropriate isolation type.","source":"<xref:System.IO.IsolatedStorage.IsolatedStorageScope> is an enumeration that enables you to create and select a store with the appropriate isolation type."},{"content":"The isolated storage classes enable you to create, enumerate, and delete isolated storage.","pos":[14958,15048]},{"content":"The methods for performing these tasks are available through the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.IO.IsolatedStorage.IsolatedStorageFile&gt;</ph> object.","pos":[15049,15174],"source":" The methods for performing these tasks are available through the <xref:System.IO.IsolatedStorage.IsolatedStorageFile> object."},{"content":"Some operations require you to have the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission&gt;</ph> permission that represents the right to administer isolated storage; you might also need to have operating system rights to access the file or directory.","pos":[15175,15433],"source":" Some operations require you to have the <xref:System.Security.Permissions.IsolatedStorageFilePermission> permission that represents the right to administer isolated storage; you might also need to have operating system rights to access the file or directory."},{"pos":[15435,15574],"content":"For a series of examples that demonstrate common isolated storage tasks, see the how-to topics listed in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Related Topics<ept id=\"p1\">](#related_topics)</ept>.","source":"For a series of examples that demonstrate common isolated storage tasks, see the how-to topics listed in [Related Topics](#related_topics)."},{"pos":[15626,15656],"content":"Scenarios for Isolated Storage","linkify":"Scenarios for Isolated Storage","nodes":[{"content":"Scenarios for Isolated Storage","pos":[0,30]}]},{"content":"Isolated storage is useful in many situations, including these four scenarios:","pos":[15658,15736]},{"content":"Downloaded controls.","pos":[15740,15760]},{"content":"Managed code controls downloaded from the Internet are not allowed to write to the hard drive through normal I/O classes, but they can use isolated storage to persist users' settings and application states.","pos":[15761,15967]},{"content":"Shared component storage.","pos":[15971,15996]},{"content":"Components that are shared between applications can use isolated storage to provide controlled access to data stores.","pos":[15997,16114]},{"content":"Server storage.","pos":[16118,16133]},{"content":"Server applications can use isolated storage to provide individual stores for a large number of users making requests to the application.","pos":[16134,16271]},{"content":"Because isolated storage is always segregated by user, the server must impersonate the user making the request.","pos":[16272,16383]},{"content":"In this case, data is isolated based on the identity of the principal, which is the same identity the application uses to distinguish between its users.","pos":[16384,16536]},{"content":"Roaming.","pos":[16540,16548]},{"content":"Applications can also use isolated storage with roaming user profiles.","pos":[16549,16619]},{"content":"This allows a user's isolated stores to roam with the profile.","pos":[16620,16682]},{"content":"You should not use isolated storage in the following situations:","pos":[16684,16748]},{"content":"To store high-value secrets, such as unencrypted keys or passwords, because isolated storage is not protected from highly trusted code, from unmanaged code, or from trusted users of the computer.","pos":[16752,16947]},{"content":"To store code.","pos":[16951,16965]},{"content":"To store configuration and deployment settings, which administrators control.","pos":[16969,17046]},{"content":"(User preferences are not considered to be configuration settings because administrators do not control them.)","pos":[17047,17157]},{"content":"Many applications use a database to store and isolate data, in which case one or more rows in a database might represent storage for a specific user.","pos":[17159,17308]},{"content":"You might choose to use isolated storage instead of a database when the number of users is small, when the overhead of using a database is significant, or when no database facility exists.","pos":[17309,17497]},{"content":"Also, when the application requires storage that is more flexible and complex than what a row in a database provides, isolated storage can provide a viable alternative.","pos":[17498,17666]},{"pos":[17702,17716],"content":"Related Topics","linkify":"Related Topics","nodes":[{"content":"Related Topics","pos":[0,14]}]},{"content":"Title","pos":[17719,17724]},{"content":"Description","pos":[17725,17736]},{"pos":[17771,17840],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Types of Isolation<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/standard/io/types-of-isolation.md)</ept>","source":"[Types of Isolation](../../../docs/standard/io/types-of-isolation.md)"},{"content":"Describes the different types of isolation.","pos":[17841,17884]},{"pos":[17887,18003],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How to: Obtain Stores for Isolated Storage<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/standard/io/how-to-obtain-stores-for-isolated-storage.md)</ept>","source":"[How to: Obtain Stores for Isolated Storage](../../../docs/standard/io/how-to-obtain-stores-for-isolated-storage.md)"},{"pos":[18004,18144],"content":"Provides an example of using the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.IO.IsolatedStorage.IsolatedStorageFile&gt;</ph> class to obtain a store isolated by user and assembly.","source":"Provides an example of using the <xref:System.IO.IsolatedStorage.IsolatedStorageFile> class to obtain a store isolated by user and assembly."},{"pos":[18147,18269],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How to: Enumerate Stores for Isolated Storage<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/standard/io/how-to-enumerate-stores-for-isolated-storage.md)</ept>","source":"[How to: Enumerate Store